{#
Optional quick-nav include for an extension (legacy Jinja2 / Markdown pipeline).

NOTE: This file is for the legacy Jinja2 → Markdown rendering path only.
In the Astro site (astro/), section navigation is handled automatically by the
floating nav in astro/src/pages/daily/[date].astro — no per-extension file needed.

What this file is for (legacy path):
- Add extra links below the section entry in the daily quick-nav
- Link to subsections, tags, categories, anchors, or custom views

How it is used (legacy path):
- templates/daily.md.j2 includes this file inside the nav list for the current
  section:
    {% include "extensions/" + sec.key + "/nav.md.j2" ignore missing %}
- The current section is available as `sec`.

Safe default:
- Delete this file if your extension has no subsection anchors or extra navigation.
- For the Astro site, no per-extension nav file is needed.

Minimal example:
  {% if sec["items"] %}
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#{{ sec.key }}-top">Top items</a></li>
    <li><a href="#{{ sec.key }}-latest">Latest items</a></li>
  </ul>
  {% endif %}
#}
